Write a program that takes a list of numbers (for example, a = [5, 10, 15, 20, 25]) and makes a new list 
of only the first and last elements of the given list. For practice, write this code inside a function.

Link: http://www.practicepython.org/exercise/2014/04/25/12-list-ends.html


My Solution:

#http://www.practicepython.org/exercise/2014/04/25/12-list-ends.html
#Check Primality Function
#Author: Calvin Tong
#Date: 29-DEC-2016
#Python version: 2.7.10.12

'''
Write a program that takes a list of numbers (for example, a = [5, 10, 15, 20, 25]) and makes a new list of only the first and last elements of the given list. 
For practice, write this code inside a function.
'''

def f_NewList(x):
	y = x[::len(x)-1]  #The other approach [x[0], x[-1]]
	return y

varList = [5, 10, 15, 20, 25]
varResult = f_NewList(varList)
print varResult
